ve revolt is recast for a twenty-first century audience.The first academic volume looking at various themes of the premium cable TV series SpartacusIncludes original, innovative research in fields of history, politics, gender, film, fan culture Explores the theme of Spartacus on screen from multiple angles: history, classics, film studies, reception studies, gender studies, fandom studies  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aSpartacus,--71 B.C.-On television. 4aClassics & Ancient History. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Rome.2bisacsh1 aAugoustakis, Antony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCyrino, Monica S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCyrino, Monica, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDaugherty, Gregory N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFutrell, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGardner, Hunter H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarrisson, Juliette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaurice, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcAuley, Alex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPotter, Amanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrince, Meredith D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaucci, Stacie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimões Rodrigues, Nuno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrong, Anise K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107